						               													<description>A unique, educational game that challenges a player's knowledge of hunting with educational facts, the luck of rolling the Dice, and Plenty of Fun.  Your goal is to collect the items you need for hunting and on your travels hunt game like deer, bears, and other animals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object:  the object of the game is to complete the entire trail, survive Wolf-Ridge, and get back to camp with the following items.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1.  Deer and license (Deer must be bagged in Large Chopping/Hardwood hill&amp;#10;2.  Wild Duck and License (Wild Duck must be obtained in Saw Mill Lake Area)&amp;#10;3.  Moose and License (Moose Must be bagged in Rubber Boot Bog Area)&amp;#10;4.  Bear and License (Bear must be bagged in Bear Claw Pass Area)&amp;#10;5. Waterproof matches&amp;#10;6. Hunting Knife&amp;#10;7. Compass&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules of the game:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Before a hunter can shoot any animals, they must first obtain a hunting license by landing on a hunting license square.  After obtaining a hunting license the hunter must then land on a shooting spot correctly answering a skill-tested question from the Game Warden's Question Hand Book in order to bag their animal.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order for the hunter to finish the game and return to camp he/she must roll the exact number of squares to finish the trail.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
